In the matter of James R. McINTYRE, Bankrupt. UNION JOINT STOCK LAND BANK OF DETROIT, Mich., Appellant, v. James R. McINTYRE, Bankrupt, Appellee. No. 7082. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Oct. 13, 1939. Edwin B. Goldsmith, of Pittsburgh, Pa., and A. G. Masters, of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. Charles E. Harrington, of Kittanning, Pa., for appellee.

Before BIGGS, MARIS, and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order of the court below, 23 F.Supp. 342, is affirmed.
